The paper deals with the problem of evading automatic face detection and recognition systems, which is a core topic in computer vision (cs.CV). It also touches upon privacy concerns and the need for user protection, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The authors use machine learning techniques to evaluate the effectiveness of different evasion techniques, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of social networks and their automatic face recognition systems on user privacy, which is a topic in information retrieval (cs.IR).
